From 1099dd417af3169f06df88b86b1f714fecce31ea Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lars Op den Kamp <lars@opdenkamp.eu>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 18:31:35 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] [depends] bump libcec to 8.1.0

libcec 8.x provides, upstream, everything the depends patches used to add, so
they are all gone and cec builds with plain CMake options:

- client applications  -> -DDISABLE_CLIENT=ON
- build metadata       -> -DDISABLE_BUILDINFO=ON
- static library       -> -DDISABLE_STATIC=ON
- flat install layout  -> -DCMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR=lib / -DCMAKE_INSTALL_INCLUDEDIR=include
- a CMake package config for find_package(libcec)

The last downstream change (an MSVC pdb tweak) is unnecessary too: the upstream
pdb install is OPTIONAL, so it can't fail whatever the compile flags produce.

libcec 8.x also dropped its p8-platform dependency, so cec no longer needs it:
drop the P8Platform find/build hooks from FindCEC.cmake and the "cec: p8-platform"
order from the depends Makefile. p8-platform stays in the tree for the binary
addons that still use it.

Bump CEC-VERSION and pass the options from the depends Makefile and
FindCEC.cmake; drop the 001/002/003 patches. The SHA512 is the sha512sum of
github.com/Pulse-Eight/libcec archive/refs/tags/libcec-8.1.0.tar.gz.
